Prince Dayo Adeyeye, who came second in the PDP governorship primaries on Tuesday has dumped the party.Â 

Adeyeye, who scored 771 votes said he could not work with the governor, Mr. Ayodele Fayose, whom he alleged imposed his deputy as the party's candidate in the July 14 governorship election. But Adeyeye, who made the disclosure while addressing his supporters at his campaign office, however said he was yet to conclude his next political platform.